        <p>Converts the cursor to Arrow mode, which lets you create a curvy arrow shape. After you select this button, you can click anywhere in the <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic,Products.MovieSync">frame</MadCap:conditionalText> to identify the starting point for the arrow. When you move the cursor, a straight line shows where the arrow will be placed. When you release the cursor, an arrow is created. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture,Products.Mimic">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../UI_Elements/Arrow_Properties_Dialog.htm" target="" title="" alt="">Arrow Properties Dialog</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
